description: Erection of 36 storey building and two eight storey buildings to provide 308 residential units up to 845 sq.m. of mixed use commercial (Use Class A1/A3/B1/D2), basement car parking for up to 78 cars and ancillary plant rooms.  The application also includes the creation of a new pedestrian/vehicular access from Graham Street and new open space accessible to the public.
decision_conditions:
CONDITION:  Prior to construction a sustainability report shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and shall be implemented and retained thereon to the satisfaction of the Local Planning Authority.  This report shall show how the following can be achieved:
- The development hereby approved will achieve at least a 'Very Good' rating under the BREEAM (BRE Environmental Assessment Method) Ecohomes Scheme.  This rating shall be achieved at all stages of the development.  
- Carbon Indexing of the residential units will be an average of 8.6, with 8.0 as a minimum. 
- Detailed calculations for determining the Carbon Index and BRE's Ecohomes rating shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. 

REASON:  To promote sustainability and energy efficiency
